[[File:宮ノ前横穴墓群-2.jpg|thumb|250px|Kamakura-style of the {{ill|Miyanomae Tunnel Tomb Cluster|ja|宮ノ前横穴墓群|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. Since most of the {{ill|Senshido|ja|羨道|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and {{ill|Genshitsu|ja|玄室|qq=draft|qq=draft}} at the front have collapsed, the inner "coffin chamber" is easily visible. '''Kamakura-style Tunnel Tomb''' (鎌倉型横穴墓) refers to a type of {{ill|Cave tomb|ja|横穴墓|qq=draft|qq=draft}} constructed from the {{ill|Kofun Period|ja|古墳時代|qq=draft|qq=draft}} to the early {{ill|Nara Period|ja|奈良時代|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, found in the former {{ill|Kamakura District|ja|鎌倉郡|qq=draft|qq=draft}}—present-day {{ill|Kanagawa Prefecture|ja|神奈川県|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Kamakura City|ja|鎌倉市|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, and their surrounding areas. It is characterized by having a “coffin chamber” excavated into the rear wall of the {{ill|Genshitsu|ja|玄室|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, and is also known as the “Kaji-ga-tani-style Tunnel Tomb.”
==Design== In Kanagawa Prefecture, many cave-type cemeteries—referred to as “Tunnel Tomb Clusters”—were constructed on mountainsides from the Kofun Period to the early Nara Period. The design known as the “Kamakura-style” is characterized by a mortuary passage (入口) leading from the {{ill|Senshido|ja|羨道|qq=draft|qq=draft}} into the burial chamber ({{ill|Genshitsu|ja|玄室|qq=draft|qq=draft}}), which features an elongated trapezoidal floor and a ceiling in the shape of a {{ill|Kamaboko|ja|蒲鉾|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. In addition, a small room resembling a shelf, known as the “coffin chamber” (棺室), is excavated into the back wall.
Incidentally, during the {{ill|Kamakura Period|ja|鎌倉時代|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, a rectangular cave-type cemetery known as a {{ill|Yagura|ja|やぐら|qq=draft|qq=draft}} was also built in Kamakura; however, there is no systematic relationship between the tunnel tombs and the yagura.<ref name="#1">栄区地域振興課『栄の歴史』（2013rd year ）20-21ページ</ref>
==Evolution of the Name== In the past, these tombs were frequently discovered in the basin of the {{ill|Kassakawa|ja|㹨川|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, which flows through southeastern Kanagawa Prefecture, particularly in the area of {{ill|Yokohama City|ja|横浜市|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and {{ill|Sakae Ward|ja|栄区|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. They were named after the local area {{ill|Kaji-ga-tani|ja|鍛冶ケ谷|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, being called “Kaji-ga-tani-style.” However, research conducted around 2004 (Heisei 16) revealed that these tombs are widespread mainly in the area centered on Kamakura City within the former {{ill|Kamakura District|ja|鎌倉郡|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, leading to the adoption of the name “Kamakura-style.”<ref name="#1"/><ref>埋蔵文化財センター（横浜市）『栄区の重要遺跡』（2015th year ）20-30ページ</ref>
==Examples of Kamakura-style Tunnel Tombs== * {{ill|Kassakawa Basin Tunnel Tomb Cluster|ja|㹨川流域横穴墓群|qq=draft|qq=draft}} ** {{ill|Nanasekiyama Tunnel Tomb Cluster|ja|七石山横穴墓群|qq=draft|qq=draft}} ・ {{ill|Miyanomae Tunnel Tomb Cluster|ja|宮ノ前横穴墓群|qq=draft|qq=draft}}<ref>埋蔵文化財センター（横浜市）『埋文よこはま31』（2015th year ）1-3ページ</ref>
==Books with Detailed Information== * {{ill|Kugenuma Girls' High School|ja|鵠沼女子高等学校|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 地歴研究部 『横浜市戸塚区㹨川流域の横穴群について』1964th year （昭和39th year ）3月20日発行 * 神奈川県考古学会 『考古論叢神奈河 12集』（田村良照「相模の横穴墓」）2004th year （平成16th year ）4月発行 * {{ill|Yokohama City Buried Cultural Properties Center|ja|埋蔵文化財センター (横浜市)|lt=Yokohama City Buried Cultural Properties Center|lt_ja=埋蔵文化財センター（横浜市）|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 『[https://www.rekihaku.city.yokohama.jp/cms_files_maibun/pr_brochure/my031-hi.pdf 埋文よこはま31号（㹨川流域の横穴墓群）]』 2015th year （平成27th year ）3月20日発行
